## Actions

| # | Action | Scope |
|---|--------|-------|
| 1 | Revoke warehouse USAGE | All warehouses in account |
| 2 | Revoke database USAGE | All databases in account |
| 3 | Re-grant exceptions | Listed below |

## Exceptions

The following objects will retain PUBLIC access:

{%- if rbac_public_exceptions | length > 0 %}
| Object | Reason |
|--------|--------|
{%- for exception in rbac_public_exceptions %}
| `{{ exception | upper }}` | Configured exception |
{%- endfor %}
{%- else %}

No exceptions configured. All PUBLIC grants will be revoked.
{%- endif %}

## Impact

After applying these changes:
- Users with only the PUBLIC role will have no warehouse, database, or schema access
- All data access must flow through explicitly granted functional roles (READ, WRITE, CREATE, ADMIN)
- Service accounts must have dedicated role grants
- BI tools and applications must authenticate with role-assigned users

## Verification

Run `SHOW GRANTS TO ROLE PUBLIC;` after applying to confirm only exceptions remain.

{%- else %}

